# CROSS-LANGUAGE CLI LIBRARY TAXONOMY MILESTONE — RUST CROSSES TO 55
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# With this completion the cross-language CLI library taxonomy documents
# the 55TH Rust CLI library variant.  Rust climbs from 54 to 55 documented
# libraries (tracing via evebox).  Rust **BREAKS the fifth triple-tie
# at 54** (Rust=Go=TS-Node=54 since R588) to take SOLO LEAD again.  New
# leaderboard: Rust=55, Go=54, TypeScript-Node=54 (Rust SOLO at 55,
# Go+TS-Node tied at 54 — ninth time Rust has taken solo lead in this
# round-sequence).  Taxonomy now spans 329 cross-language CLI library
# variants across 80 documented languages.
#
# Pattern: 1 new language (R589 Boo/booc) → R590 Rust=55 (tracing THIS)
# → expected R591 Go=55 → expected R592 TS-Node=55.  This is the 1st
# of 3 leader bumps in the current segment.
#
# This completion EXPANDS Axis 9 (UNIFIED LOGGING / OBSERVABILITY)
# within Rust.  Rust now has THREE documented Axis 9 variants —
# matching TS-Node's count (consola + winston + pino) and Go's count
# (zap + zerolog + logrus):
#   - env_logger (rust-cli/env_logger) — R582 (trail) — simple
#     RUST_LOG-driven log facade implementation
#   - slog (slog-rs/slog) — R586 (afterburn) — pre-tracing-era
#     structured logging with drain composition (2014)
#   - tracing (tokio-rs/tracing) — R590 (THIS) — MODERN
#     STRUCTURED EVENT + SPAN OBSERVABILITY designed for async
#     Rust; the de-facto standard for tokio-ecosystem services
#
# These three libraries occupy distinct slots within Axis 9 Rust:
#   env_logger = SIMPLE app-level logging via RUST_LOG env var
#   slog       = pre-tracing structured logging with drains
#   tracing    = MODERN structured-event + span observability
#                  with async-aware context propagation
#
# Axis 9 cross-language coverage as of R590:
#   - TS-Node: consola + winston + pino (three variants)
#   - Go: zap + zerolog + logrus (three variants)
#   - Rust: env_logger + slog + tracing (three variants — MATCHES)
#
# All three top-tier languages now have THREE documented Axis 9
# variants each — a clean symmetric coverage across the unified
# logging / observability dimension.
