#   util         Utility subcommands
#   version      Display version
#
# Five-axis distinctness from every other documented Rust logger:
#
#   1. SPAN-BASED CONTEXT BLOCKS — Every other documented Rust
#      logger uses per-call structured fields.  tracing has
#      SPANS as time-bounded context blocks that nest
#      hierarchically + carry typed fields automatically.
#
#   2. ASYNC-AWARE CONTEXT PROPAGATION — Every other documented
#      Rust logger has no async-await integration.  tracing
#      pauses + resumes spans automatically across `.await`
#      points + tokio task spawning.
#
#   3. SUBSCRIBER + LAYER COMPOSITION ARCHITECTURE — Every
#      other documented Rust logger has monolithic output or
#      simple drain chains.  tracing has Subscriber trait +
#      Layer composition with OpenTelemetry-native integration.
#
#   4. ATTRIBUTE-BASED INSTRUMENTATION — Every other documented
#      Rust logger requires manual sub-logger / span creation
#      at function entry.  tracing's `#[instrument]` proc-macro
#      attribute auto-wraps functions.
#
#   5. TOKIO-ECOSYSTEM FOUNDATIONAL PROVENANCE — Every other
#      documented Rust logger has different ecosystem provenance.
#      tracing is the de-facto observability standard for the
#      tokio + async-Rust ecosystem (axum/tonic/sqlx/AWS-SDK-
#      Rust/Cloudflare/Vector/Linkerd).
